quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  44,1,"Ha Mīm."
  44,2,"By the Evident Scripture,"
  44,3,"We have indeed sent it down on a blessed night{1}. Indeed, We have always been warning.",footnotes:1:This night is known as the night of <i>Qadr </i>(Surah number 97), in the month of Ramadan.
  44,4,"Onit, every wise command is distinguished—"
  44,5,"a command from Us; indeed, We have always been sending"
  44,6,"mercy from your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord—indeed, it is He who is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing—"
  44,7,"<i class=""s"">(from the) </i><span class="h">Lord{1}</span>of the heavens and the earth and what is between them, if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><i class=""s"">(can ever) </i>believe with certitude.",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Asem, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…the All-Knowing. <sub lang="en-GB"><small>7</small></sub>7 (He is the) Lord of the…”</span>
  44,8,"There is no god but He; He gives life and causes death—your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord and the Lord of your ancient fathers."
  44,9,"Yet they play around in doubt."
  44,10,"So wait<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>and watch out for the day when the sky produces evident smoke"
